A high quality for the value.	I would be prepared to pay full price for this hotel, considering the service, location, and overall quality.	Its not luxurious, but for the total price of $160 found it was reasonably priced for the location.	I booked this room on Priceline for $66--with that price I shouldn't complain at all.	The only two negatives I would say were the price for parking and the slow internet speed.	This hotel was the most reasonably price in Seattle for its category and its outstanding downtown location.